[[File:Mort myre fungus detail.png|left|100px]]
'''Mort myre fungi''' are mushrooms native to the [[Mort Myre Swamp]] in [[Morytania]]. They can be obtained by casting [[bloom]] with either a [[Silver sickle (b)|blessed silver sickle]] or an [[Ivandis flail]] near some dead logs, which may or may not grow the fungi. They can also be obtained by [[#Drop sources|killing monsters]] or as produce from certain [[Zygomite (player-owned farm)|zygomite breeds]] at the [[player-owned farm]]. The quest [[Nature Spirit]] is required to obtain a blessed silver sickle, thus making it an indirect requirement for a player to grow their own fungus. Completion of the [[Morytania achievements#Easy tasks|easy Morytania tasks]] allows players to gain double fungi while wearing [[Morytania legs 1]] or better.

Casting bloom will drain [[prayer]] points from the caster, up to a maximum of 60. The prayer drain is not affected by the quantity of items produced. 

The fungus can be used to fill a [[druid pouch]], which turns [[ghast]]s visible and attackable. It counts as 1 harvest for filling the pouch. The fungus is also used as a secondary for [[super energy]] potions, created at level 52 [[Herblore]], which makes them popular amongst players for easy Herblore training.

During [[While Guthix Sleeps]], Mort Myre fungus may be provided by freeing a [[Druid Spirit]] along with [[clean avantoe]] (ingredients to make a [[Super energy|Super energy potion]]) to place on the Statue representing Energy. Players have to be careful that their Druid pouch doesn't use up the mushroom during this process unless they have already obtained the [[Dolmen]] from the Energy statue, as they will have to obtain one manually.

They are also used as food for [[Zygomite (player-owned farm)|Zygomites (player-owned farm)]] and the [[Broav]] pet which was released with [[While Guthix Sleeps]].

