[[File:Phoenix feather detail.png|60px|left]]
'''Phoenix feathers''' can be plucked from the [[desert phoenix]] located along the north-western bank of the [[River Elid]], in the gorge west of the [[Dominion Tower]]. Plucking attempts may fail, in which case the phoenix will stun and deals damage to the player. When a feather is successfully plucked the player earns 26 [[Thieving]] experience. They can also occasionally be obtained from a [[forge phoenix]] or a [[divine forge phoenix]].

A phoenix feather is used on [[black mushroom ink]] in [[The Golem]] quest to turn it into a [[phoenix quill pen]]. It is also an ingredient used in combination with an [[antifire (3)]] potion to create a [[super antifire (3)]] potion at level 85 [[Herblore]]. This potion renders the user completely immune to [[dragonfire]] for 6 minutes. It is also a necessary material in the restoration of the [[Ceremonial plume (damaged)]] artefact, requiring 81 [[Archaeology]]. 

Plucking feathers from the desert phoenix is the most reliable way to obtain large amounts of feathers. [[The Golem]] quest must be completed to be able to obtain additional phoenix feathers. Two feathers are plucked with each action after completing the [[elite Desert achievements]]. Phoenix feathers can be stored in [[Beast of Burden]] familiars, can be banked using [[signs of the porter]], or noted using [[magic notepaper]] (although the feathers must be used on the notepaper, not vice versa). The [[Thieving cape]] perk works on phoenix feathers; and other [[Thieving training|Thieving boosts]] will increase success rate while gathering feathers. The [[Sticky Fingers]] relic power does not work on the desert phoenix. With lower Thieving and/or [[Constitution]] levels, players may need to bring [[food]] to heal damage dealt by unsuccessful Thieving attempts. Protection from the [[desert heat]] is also needed in the area where the desert phoenix is located, unless the [[Crocodile Tears]] quest has been completed.

