A '''blue charm''' is the highest-tier charm of the four primary [[charms|charm types]] used in the [[Summoning]] skill to create [[Summoning pouches]]. The use of blue charms in the creation of summoning pouches requires Summoning level 19. The amount of experience gained from creating pouches that use blue charms varies from 59.7 to 783.2 each, depending on the [[summoning pouches|pouch]] being created. Blue charms are the rarest of the four primary Summoning charms, and are generally referred to as the best charm for training the Summoning skill, along with [[crimson charms]].

Some of the more popular methods of obtaining blue charms include killing monsters in the first portion of [[The Shadow Reef]], killing the [[Arch-Glacor]] on normal mode with no modifiers, killing [[Bork]] and [[Tormented demon]]s. Using [[charming potion]]s will increase the base number of charms dropped by a monster by 1 for 6 minutes. [[Charm sprite]]s also have a relatively high drop rate, for players with level 72 [[Hunter]].

Blue charms may also be purchased using [[Zeal]] obtained from the [[Soul Wars]] minigame.
Additionally, [[Spirit gems]] may be used to save these charms when creating [[summoning pouches]].
The [[Charming Imp]] may be used to automatically collect these charms when dropped by a monster.

As with the other three primary charm types, blue charms may be used in [[Dungeoneering]] to summon [[Dungeoneering/Summoning|familiars]].

